source applies] to the RT-AC68U, RT-AC68U v2, RT-AC69U. {{WiFiCert|WFA56214|12/15/2014}} ==T-Mobile Personal Cellspot Router== ===Support=== * [[ASUS TM-AC1900]] [http://www.asus.com/supportonly/TM-AC1900/ Support page] * [https://support.t-mobile.com/community/coverage/personal-cellspot/wi-fi-cellspot-router '''T-Mobile''' Support page] * [http://cellspotroutersetup.t-mobile.com/ Wi-Fi CellSpot Router setup] * [[ASUS RT-AC68U]] [http://www.asus.com/Networking/RTAC68U/ Product Page] http://cellspot.router :Default username is '''admin''' and password is '''password'''. ===Firmware=== *Latest firmware is 3.0.0.4.376_3199. Firmware notes... :Fix CVE-2016-0802 :ACSD: fix no 5ghz auto channel select issue :Samba: fix Badlock bug :Fix possibe memory leak :Fix LPR buffer overflow issue :Fix XSS issue in WDS page :Dropbear: update to version 2016.74 :Openssl: update to version 1.0.2j :Fix nat table chaos caused by miniupnp ===Information=== *T-Mobile released a wireless router rebranded from the RT-AC68U. :The T-Mobile rebranded version has a custom proprietary firmware :that is modified for optimizing the T-Mobile Wi-Fi calling feature. :This router requires a refundable $25 deposit (or none if qualified) for postpaid :plan customers [$99 for retail pricing/prepaid accounts] since this is a lease. *''Notice'': If you got this router as a postpaid customer, keep in mind that T-Mobile expects :it back after you cancel your T-Mobile service or if a coverage line is disconnected :from a family/multiple line account within 45 days after cancellation/disconnection. :Failure to do so may incur a $99 non-return fee. If the router is returned damaged, $25. :[This doesn't apply to prepaid customers or if bought in retail price.] ===See also=== {{ASUS AC products}} __NOTOC__
